<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                        <head>No. 589.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S.
                                    Sackville West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-07-31"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 31, 1888</date>.
                                (Received August 2.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of 23d instant, and to inform you that I have
                            brought the alleged discrimination against American vessels passing
                            through the Welland Canal to the notice of the Canadian Government.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville
                                    West.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>